sequenceDiagram
    autonumber
    actor User as User / Operator
    participant O as CLI / GUI Orchestrators (current)
    participant SCN as Directory Scanner
    participant EXT as File Router
    participant WRK as Worker Pool / Python Scripts
    participant META as Metadata Extractor
    participant FEAT as Feature Builder (compromise NLP)
    participant ANA as Analytics Engines (Descriptive/Diagnostic/Predictive/Prescriptive)
    participant OUT as Output Delivery (JSON, Markdown, CSV, Web Dashboard)
    participant PLN as Planned Expansion (Issues #19, #20, #21)

    User->>O: Start analysis (source folder, options)
    O->>SCN: Scan source folder (read-only)
    SCN-->>O: File manifest

    loop For each file
        O->>EXT: Route by type
        alt Text/Document (.txt, .md, .csv, .log, .json, .pdf)
            EXT->>WRK: Extract text (worker_threads / pdf-parse / OCR)
        alt Image (.png, .jpg, .jpeg)
            EXT->>WRK: Extract text (worker_threads / tesseract.js OCR)
        alt Video (.mp4)
            EXT->>WRK: Process video (Python keyframe OCR + Whisper transcription)
        end
        EXT->>META: Extract metadata (mtime, path, size, PDF author)
        WRK-->>O: Text content
        META-->>O: Metadata payload
    end

    O->>FEAT: Normalize text + extract NLP entities (dates, locations)
    FEAT-->>O: Normalised corpus & features

    O->>ANA: Run Descriptive, Diagnostic, Predictive, & Prescriptive models
    ANA-->>O: Glossaries, TF-IDF matrices, moving averages, warnings

    O->>OUT: Deliver report (JSON stdout, Markdown file, CSV spreadsheet, or GUI page)
    OUT-->>User: Visual telemetry report & recommendations

    Note over PLN: Future work includes unified audio files, visual object/motion video tracking, and stemming condensation.
